# Files here are NEVER uploaded to Vercel — they can't be reached at any URL.
# They stay on your Mac and still work locally (python3 -m http.server 8080).
#
# UPDATED 23 Jul 2026 — Dominic: "publish everything". Every HTML page and the
# compliance endpoint that used to be blocked are now PUBLISHED, so all the
# dashboard tabs and planning-page links resolve. Money / rates / compliance are
# therefore reachable by anyone who has the (private, unguessable) URL — that was
# the explicit choice, to be locked down properly when the staff login goes in.
#
# What stays blocked below is deliberately NOT web pages: secrets, the internal
# operating docs and persona prompts, and the research library. Publishing those
# would expose the whole operating system and the do-not-claim register on the
# public URL. Delete a line to publish it.

# ---- Secrets — NEVER deploy ----
.env.local
.env

# ---- Internal operating docs, persona prompts, research library (NOT web pages) ----
*.md
team/
docs/

# ---- Build scripts & local render previews (not web assets) ----
_preview/
make-menu-pdf.py
